00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:26,520
Jim, my old friend! Jim.
Help, please.

261
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:29,040
Wait. Wait.

262
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,880
Give us a minute.

263
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:37,720
Thank God, you're here.

264
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,600
You have to help me.

265
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:42,200
They're torturing me.

266
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,880
Torture is what you do.

267
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,360
The doctors here are trying
to help you.

268
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:47,600
It's torture, I'm telling you!

269
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:49,040
I don't see any signs of it.

270
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:51,560
It's mental torture!

271
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,280
It's therapy.

272
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,320
You're insane, remember?

273
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,840
That's what your lawyers said anyhow.

274
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:00,080
Goodbye, Penguin.

275
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,720
You owe me, Jim Gordan.

276
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,280
I lied for you!

277
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:11,200
He killed Galavan! Not me!
It was him! It was him!

278
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:15,720
<i>You owe me, Jim Gordan.
I lied for you!</i>

279
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:20,320
<i>He killed Galavan! Not me!
It was him! It was him!</i>

280
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,080
<i>It was him!</i>

281
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:34,160
I should say, that's learned him
Master Bruce.

282
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,120
We're supposed to have
a training session.

283
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:40,880
Yeah. Well, I got held up
in the city, didn't I?

284
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,720
Besides, I thought your chat
with Dr. Thompkins

285
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:43,800
would keep you occupied.

286
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:45,760
And I thought you were
against therapy.

287
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:48,920
Well, that's before I realized
you're still keen on keeping secrets.

288
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,720
If I'd told you what Selina
and I had planned,

289
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:51,880
you would have stopped me.

290
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,480
Because I didn't I got the name
of my parents' killer from Silver.

291
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:57,520
Then you made us leave Gotham.

292
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,920
We lost more than a month we could
have spent searching for M. Malone.

293
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,280
We left the city

294
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,840
because you were at the end
of your emotional and physical rope.

295
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:06,800
And quite frankly, you're incapable
of catching a common cold

296
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:07,920
let alone a killer.

297
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,760
Will you, will you stop?

298
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,800
Now, I need to ask you
a very important question.

299
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:18,720
Are we in this together...

300
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,240
or not?

301
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:25,120
Yes.

302
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,480
We're in this together.

303
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:31,560
Right, well, I told you
I had some business in the city.

304
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,400
I went to see a sergeant I know

305
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:36,120
and we did some digging
in some GCPD files

306
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,280
for any M. Malones that fit
our particulars.

307
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,760
Age, size, height, race.

308
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:44,520
Whether they were free during
the murder of your parents.

309
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:45,680
And?

310
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,800
Patrick Malone.

311
00:17:56,720 --> 00:18:00,600
Goes by the nickname, Matches.

312
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:04,480
Delightful chap really, committed
his first murder when he was 15.

313
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:07,240
Suspected of half a dozen since.

314
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:09,040
Now, I need to ask you.

315
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:13,320
If you were in charge, what next?

316
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:15,520
You could've gotten this information
from Detective Gordon.

317
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,680
Why didn't you contact him?

318
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:19,160
I'm the one asking the questions now,
Master Bruce.

319
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:23,280
We find this man,
what do you plan to do?

320
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,680
- Kill him.
- No.

321
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:36,560
- You can't stop me.
- I bloody can, and I will.

322
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:40,280
You're too young to have a death
on your conscience, Master Bruce.

323
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:44,200
- But, but...
- I know your parents deserve justice

324
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,200
and I know you're not gonna
stop till you find it.

325
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:51,400
But when we find this Malone,
I will kill him and not you.

326
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:52,520
That is the deal.

327
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,520
Do you accept?

328
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:59,880
- Yes.
- Say it.

329
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:02,400
We find him.

330
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:05,320
We make him talk.

331
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,400
You kill him.

332
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,400
You have no idea what you're missing.

333
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Bitch.

334
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:37,800
Where am I?

335
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,560
Where am I?

336
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:44,440
Nora. Try not to exert yourself.

337
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:45,880
You're in a hospital.

338
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,000
Who are you?

339
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:49,560
This is not Gotham General.

340
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:52,680
No. You're in a more secure place.

341
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:55,960
I'm Doctor Thompkins Lee.

342
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,360
They're scared of Victor.

343
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,400
Yes.

344
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,680
Victor only did these terrible things
because of me.

345
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:09,960
You're not responsible
for your husband's actions .

346
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:12,080
He's not an evil man.

347
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:16,320
He believes the good of saving me
outweighs the bad of his actions.

348
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,760
I understand.

349
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,920
But he's not my concern right now,
you are.

350
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,440
And you have to try and stay calm.

351
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:24,160
You're stable
but you're still very fragile.

352
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,720
I could have saved him.

353
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,520
I saw him going down this path.

354
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,720
Becoming more and more obsessed.

355
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,960
Why didn't I do something?

356
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:42,320
I know what you mean.

357
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:44,880
It's hard when you love someone.

358
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:49,120
You see the person that they were,
the person they could still become.

359
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,360
You close your eyes to the truth.

360
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,560
He's coming for me, isn't he?

361
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:04,440
The police think so.

362
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:06,560
So stubborn, my Victor.

363
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:11,080
- You're pregnant.
- Yes.

364
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:13,480
Do you know yet if it's a boy
or a girl?

365
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:15,160
Not yet.

366
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:18,000
I always wanted a girl.

367
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,960
You shouldn't be here.

368
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:28,320
Let's focus on you
and not worry about me. Okay?

369
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:39,280
Winter stakeout at the loony bin.
Fabulous.

370
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:42,440
Nora doesn't have long.
Fries knows that.

371
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:44,360
- He'll come soon.
- He'd better.

372
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:49,400
We could freeze to death waiting.
Which would be ironic.

373
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,280
You hear that?

374
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:04,200
Take cover!

375
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:06,200
Let's go. Heads up! Eyes Open.

376
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,360
Open fire.

377
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:23,880
Move, move, keep going.
Get the door. Go.

378
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:27,560
- Hands in the air!
- I can't! I can't!

379
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:28,800
Don't shoot!

380
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,440
- Where's Victor Fries?
- I don't know!

381
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:33,440
Please! Help me!

382
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,680
Let's go. Come on.

383
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:47,320
Chloe?

384
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,080
Chloe?

385
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,880
Help me.

386
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,800
Chloe!

387
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:56,160
Mom!

388
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:26,120
Copy that. Fries took out a wall
in the east wing.

389
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:29,160
Have B-team cut him off.
We'll head directly to the infirmary.

390
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,720
Alpha to Bravo continue
pursuing suspect

391
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,240
we're heading to the infirmary.

392
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:35,080
Copy that. Maintaining pursuit.

393
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,440
Take cover!

394
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:54,520
Nora!

395
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:12,480
What the hell?

396
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,000
Go!

397
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:05,240
<i>Hello, Victor.</i>

398
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:07,840
<i>Forgive me for getting straight
to the point.</i>

399
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,400
I'm a great admirer of your work

400
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:13,720
and I would like to offer
a way out of your situation.

401
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:14,960
Who are you?

402
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:17,280
<i>I'm a friend. But, let me ask you.</i>

403
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:20,440
Once you've rescue your wife,
what is your plan?

404
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:23,360
<i>To steal a vehicle?
Blast your way out?</i>

405
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:28,200
There is a set of keys on the chair.

406
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:31,360
<i>They belong to a vehicle that
is waiting by the loading docks.</i>

407
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:36,920
How do I know it's not a trap?

408
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:39,000
It is not a trap.

409
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:40,560
It is an exchange.

410
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,920
<i>You get your wife and your freedom.</i>

411
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,640
I can keep the police at bay
while you escape,

412
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:48,200
<i>as thanks you will leave me</i>

413
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:51,960
one cartridge of your
cryonic formula.

414
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:53,720
<i>What do you say?</i>

415
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:57,280
<i>The police are coming,
you can't beat them</i>

416
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,640
<i>all and time is running out
for you...</i>

417
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,960
and for Nora.

418
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:18,400
Go fetch that,
would you Miss Peabody?

419
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,840
Fries is in the building.

420
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:29,000
We have to go.

421
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:30,320
We can't leave her.

422
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,520
The staff bailed when
the alarm went off, she'll die.

423
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,720
So we take her with us.

424
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,280
Come on.

425
00:26:37,320 --> 00:26:38,600
Careful.

426
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:43,080
Thank you.

427
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:51,280
I'll take it from here.

428
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:57,800
Victor, Victor listen to me.

429
00:26:57,880 --> 00:27:00,000
- We're trying to help her.
- You're killing her.

430
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,080
- No, no.
- Victor.

431
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:03,120
Victor, I understand why
you're doing this.

432
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:04,320
I'm saving her life.

433
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,520
At the cost of how many other lives?

434
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,400
Too many to turn back now.

435
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:14,360
Soon as I've done what I need to do,
I'll give myself up.

436
00:27:14,440 --> 00:27:15,600
But now we have to leave.

437
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:20,160
Victor, I'm a doctor,
if we move her now she might die.

438
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,560
A doctor, good.

439
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,360
You're coming with us to push
the wheelchair, let's go.

440
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,160
- No, no way!
- Jim, I'm going.

441
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,480
- She's my patient.
- I can't let you do that.

442
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:29,720
I'll go, take me.

443
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:32,400
Jim, it's not your call.
She needs me.

444
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:35,160
I'm not gonna hurt her.

445
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,920
I don't wanna hurt anyone
unless I have to.

446
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:39,080
Jim, I'm going.

447
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:41,000
Victor, please, don't do this.

448
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:45,520
Nora, don't worry,
it's all under control.

449
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:46,960
Help.

450
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:48,360
We have to go, now.

451
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,560
You, in there.

452
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,440
Do what he is saying.
We'll be okay.

453
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:54,800
Now!

454
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,160
Okay.

455
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,640
Okay, let's go!

456
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:27,760
Thank you, so much.

457
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:40,960
<i>Lee!</i>

458
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,360
<i>Lee!</i>

459
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:03,480
Apologies officers, the extreme cold
has shorted the wiring,

460
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:04,600
we're working on it.

461
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:06,480
<i>Well, work on it quick!</i>

462
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:09,440
Oh, we are, we are.

463
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:14,040
Please put that somewhere very
safe would you Ms. Peabody?

464
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:17,440
Good news officers.

465
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:25,960
Did Fries say anything,
anything at all about his plans?

466
00:29:26,040 --> 00:29:29,160
No, nothing. He just said sorry.

467
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:31,200
Yo, partner!

468
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:32,760
What'd we miss?

469
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:34,320
Fries got away with Nora and Lee.

470
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,800
I put a BOLO out on the vehicle
but that's all we got.

471
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:39,440
Fries has to put his wife on ice
as quickly as possible, right?

472
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:41,320
He can't go home
there's cops at the door,

473
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:42,800
where's he gonna go?

474
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:45,120
He's got the equipment with him.
He could freeze her anywhere.

475
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:49,120
Wait, now he could freeze her
but he can't keep her frozen,

476
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,600
not without one of those
cryo chambers he built.

477
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:52,720
Then he is going home.

478
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:54,960
It's still at his house.
They were never taken into evidence.

479
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:57,120
It's where he went, has to be.
Come on.

480
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:17,280
Victor, please think about this.

481
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,880
How will you take care of her
if you're in prison?

482
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:24,400
I won't, you will. Gotham will.
It's the law.

483
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,640
As long as she's legally alive,
she's a ward of the city

484
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,080
and the city has to keep
her alive and safe.

485
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:30,360
Victor.

486
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,960
Hey there, darling.

487
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:33,440
I've brought you home.

488
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:35,160
I'm so tired.

489
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:38,320
I know. It will all be over soon.

490
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:41,400
Victor...

491
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:45,160
I want you to let me go.

492
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,440
Let me die.

493
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:48,000
Nora, you don't mean that.

494
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:50,960
I can do this, the process works.

495
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:53,720
So I should wake up one day,
with you in prison?

496
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:55,600
Or dead?

497
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,800
A life alone isn't one that I want.

498
00:30:57,880 --> 00:30:59,960
I'll be there when you wake up.
I'll be there.

499
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:02,240
I'll find a way, I will.

500
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:03,480
There's always hope.

501
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:06,640
As long as you're alive,
there's hope, right?

502
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:13,720
Yes, there's hope.

503
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,440
Okay.

504
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:23,920
My necklace, the one that you gave me
on our first anniversary.

505
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:26,440
It's on the nightstand,

506
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,520
would you get it for me please, dear?

507
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:34,240
Go. I'm strong enough to use it
if I need to.

508
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:45,080
If you hurry you can make it out
before he gets back.

509
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,880
I'm not leaving you.

510
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,920
This must be very stressful for you
and your baby.

511
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:50,000
We're fine.

512
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,760
Could I have some water?

513
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,720
Thank you.

514
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,200
You heard him.

515
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:16,760
He's not a bad man at heart.

516
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:20,800
- You have to tell them that.
- I will.

517
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:24,200
Please tell them that I'm very sorry
for my part in this.

518
00:32:26,240 --> 00:32:29,080
I saw the man that he was becoming
and I did nothing.

519
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,800
Because I loved him.

520
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:38,360
You know what that's like, don't you?

521
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,360
I do.

522
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:45,120
Thank you.

523
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:48,360
You've been very kind.

524
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:49,760
God bless you and your baby.

525
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:53,000
Nora, I got it.

526
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,640
I've got it.

527
00:32:58,520 --> 00:32:59,720
Victor...

528
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:02,880
I love you.

529
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:07,840
Please don't blame yourself.

530
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,320
I love you.

531
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,360
See you soon.

532
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:19,960
You should stand back.

533
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,080
I felt the breeze when you came
