534
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:17,760
I'm glad you came.

535
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:19,200
I need a favor.

536
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,960
Nice to see you, Selina.

537
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:23,360
Sorry for not telling you
that I was skipping town

538
00:34:23,440 --> 00:34:25,480
to go to my castle in France.

539
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,640
It's a Chalet, in Switzerland.

540
00:34:27,720 --> 00:34:28,720
Whatever.

541
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,320
Where's the king of Snotty England?

542
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,720
Alfred went to the city.

543
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:39,960
This is the man
that Silver told us about.

544
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:41,640
Alfred tracked him down.

545
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:45,720
Patrick Mallone.

546
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,720
I thought his name started with M?

547
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:49,920
The M stands for Matris,
it's a nickname.

548
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,480
That's a lame nickname.

549
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:56,200
So you found him,
what do you need me for?

550
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:58,360
I need you to get me a gun.

551
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,960
- So, you're gonna kill him?
- Yes.

552
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:04,240
Your Butler know?

553
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:06,600
Alfred thinks he's gonna be
the one to kill him,

554
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:08,680
that's what I'm asking you.

555
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:11,760
You couldn't even push
that guy out of the window.

556
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:14,520
So how do you expect to do this?

557
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:19,200
Because this man killed my parents.

558
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:26,600
You ever even fired a gun before?

559
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:28,120
Please, Selina,
you're the only person I can...

560
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,680
You don't even know
what you're asking, Bruce.

561
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,480
Yeah, sure, the guy deserves it.

562
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:38,440
But doing this,
you won't ever, ever be the same.

563
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:43,760
That's what I'm counting on.

564
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:59,640
Crap, how'd you wanna play this one?

565
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:02,960
Slow and careful,
no gunplay if we can help it.

566
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:05,320
Set up a perimeter,
I'm gonna look inside.

567
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,160
- Roger.
- Perimeter.

568
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:09,120
Hey, set up a perimeter.

569
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:16,080
Give me one more moment, doctor.

570
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:19,640
And I'll put myself in your charge.

571
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:30,640
No.

572
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,000
No.

573
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:35,720
No. No. No. No. No. No.

574
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:36,920
Nora!

575
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,160
I don't understand, it works,
my formula works!

576
00:36:39,240 --> 00:36:40,440
How?

577
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:44,440
She switched cartridges.

578
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,560
She changed her cartridges?

579
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,200
Did you know?

580
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:51,720
Did you know she switched
the cartridges?

581
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:52,880
No.

582
00:36:56,880 --> 00:36:58,560
I'm... I'm so sorry.

583
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:02,480
<i>Mr. Fries, this is the GCPD,
you're surrounded.</i>

584
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:07,320
<i>Please come out and give yourself up
and let's avoid any more sadness.</i>

585
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:09,800
Yeah.

586
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,360
No more sadness.

587
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:18,800
Will you be very kind

588
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:21,600
and go tell the Police
that I will do as they say?

589
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,960
Nora loved you very much.

590
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:31,280
I'm envious of the bond you had.

591
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,320
GCPD.

592
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:22,640
Victor?

593
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:28,840
Oh, my God.

594
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:48,640
Hey. You should go back to bed.

595
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,200
Can't sleep.

596
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:56,880
Heard you on the phone.

597
00:38:56,960 --> 00:38:58,080
Hugo Strange called.

598
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:01,440
Victor Fries died
in Arkham infirmary.

599
00:39:01,520 --> 00:39:03,240
They couldn't revive him.

600
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:07,480
- You okay?
- I am.

601
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:10,120
Are you?

602
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,040
Wish you hadn't gone.

603
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:21,480
Wish you hadn't put our baby at risk.

604
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:25,080
You put us at risk
when you put Nora at risk.

605
00:39:25,160 --> 00:39:26,760
She was under my care.

606
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:27,960
That was different
that was Police work.

607
00:39:28,040 --> 00:39:29,600
That was you, it's all you.

608
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:31,680
Arkham was actually Barnes' idea.

609
00:39:31,760 --> 00:39:34,000
but it made sense,
it was good Police work.

610
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:36,920
What about Galavan?
Was that good Police work too?

611
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:41,080
- What about him?
- The way he died.

612
00:39:41,160 --> 00:39:43,720
Whatever the truth is,
it's not what you told me.

613
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:44,880
How do you know?

614
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:48,000
Because I know when
you're being dishonest.

615
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:49,120
And you know what?

616
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:51,320
If anybody deserves to die,
its Galavan.

617
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:54,080
Don't talk to me about Police work,

618
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:57,000
it's you, you lied to me.

619
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:21,040
I know you say
there are no hopeless cases.

620
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:22,880
And there are none.

621
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:26,960
The beauty of life can spring forward
from even the harshest of climates.

622
00:40:27,040 --> 00:40:32,160
We simply need to be more aggressive
in our treatment.

623
00:40:32,240 --> 00:40:36,200
Now, I must go see
to our newest guest.

624
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,920
Good morning, Victor.

625
00:40:57,920 --> 00:40:59,360
Where am I?

626
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:05,640
Legally your corpse is in the Arkham
morgue, but obviously you're here.

627
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:07,520
Indian Hill.

628
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:09,800
Indian Hill is a toxic waste dump.

629
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:12,640
A useful fiction.

630
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:14,240
You're the one who spoke
to me in Arkham.

631
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,560
Hugo Strange.

632
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:18,280
Pleasure to meet you face to face.

633
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:20,560
How is it I am not dead?

634
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:23,000
It's simply astonishing, isn't it?

635
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:26,800
My guess is that you absorbed some
of your formula over the past months.

636
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:29,480
Your body underwent
a profound cellular change,

637
00:41:29,560 --> 00:41:32,080
when you were brought in here,
you were actually overheating.

638
00:41:32,160 --> 00:41:35,440
Now look there, at the thermometer.

639
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:40,920
It's negative 20 degrees
and I'm not even cold.

640
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:45,120
The formula appears to have lowered
your core body temperature.

641
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:48,520
You can only survive in severe
hypothermic conditions,

642
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:51,200
anything above freezing
will kill you.

643
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:54,160
But never fear,
you won't be locked in there forever.

644
00:41:54,240 --> 00:41:57,560
We've made some modifications to your
suit to allow you to walk freely.

645
00:41:57,640 --> 00:42:01,840
For now, rest,
tomorrow we begin work.

646
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:05,160
One project in particular,
I think you will find fascinating.

647
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:07,480
I should have died with Nora.

648
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:11,840
This all should have ended.

649
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:17,440
Then take this opportunity, Victor,
pretend you did die.

650
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:20,240
Death is not an ending.

651
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:23,320
Death is a new beginning.

